blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">March 2024</a>. </p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5ca2252a-0c54-45c1-a613-20a4fd64f330_768x1058.jpeg" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/uOl39akBPvURTHmkVc0_ 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/xvMw7Kuo- 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/bG1d3EbJdVrjkoGn649pAi- 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/RNtZbZVVnA-julihBd61qN_ 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/5OIEk-psLpCWW_" width="310" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/VEQ-TcA_aGi7d0uY_ 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/12js3af3KA2MQc0jCKRQxbq6kJYybYkh_eZQ1X74sZs=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd184NDgsY19saW1pdCxmX2F1dG8scV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkY1Y2EyMjUyYS0wYzU0LTQ1YzEtYTYxMy0yMGE0ZmQ2NGYzMzBfNzY4eDEwNTguanBlZw== 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/Xw2Rl1F_ 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/5OIEk-psLpCWW_ 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"/></picture></a></figure><p></p><p>Lastly, I have another weird horror story appearing in <em><a href="https://store.mcsweeneys.net/products/mcsweeney-s-71" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">McSweeney’s 71: The Monstrous and the Terrible</a></em> edited by horror genius Brian Evenson. This issue is overflowing with some of my favorite contemporary authors of the dark and strange: Stephen Graham Jones, Mariana Enríquez, Nick Mamatas, Erika T. Wurth, Gabino Iglesias, and many more. Although I haven’t gotten my copies yet, <a href="https://twitter.com/victorlavalle/status/1707546241205154275" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">subscribers have started getting them</a> in the mail and—in usual <em>McSweeney’s</em> fashion—the issue is stunning to look at with endpaper art and three different monstrous slipcases. <a href="https://store.mcsweeneys.net/products/mcsweeney-s-71" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">You can subscribe or order here</a>.</p><p>That’s it for now. </p><p>EDITING TO ADD: Got the <em>McSweeney’s </em>today and it’s as gorgeous as advertised:</p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Facd9b5bc-1a07-4497-9369-3093ff17c08b_2048x1536.jpeg" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/ZmhrMv-PS8T59-PWRLuhhgAuVNCBmGoBLEXnH-AxuOg=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd180MjQsY19saW1pdCxmX3dlYnAscV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkZhY2Q5YjViYy0xYTA3LTQ0OTctOTM2OS0zMDkzZmYxN2MwOGJfMjA0OHgxNTM2LmpwZWc= 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/w_K-N2wcOLYf-_ 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/KkhYfwbmJ7exMIXrO4ZfWJ56iMYn4m2Y5_0_Pbq21F8=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xMjcyLGNfbGltaXQsZl93ZWJwLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGYWNkOWI1YmMtMWEwNy00NDk3LTkzNjktMzA5M2ZmMTdjMDhiXzIwNDh4MTUzNi5qcGVn 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/1jtho9hZfVfOLcmrMVmU4VxoxYdHl2_UUL81xYngvWg=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xNDU2LGNfbGltaXQsZl93ZWJwLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGYWNkOWI1YmMtMWEwNy00NDk3LTkzNjktMzA5M2ZmMTdjMDhiXzIwNDh4MTUzNi5qcGVn 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="